creating a qt C++ application

fazer o merge entre "src/editor/gui/main_window/ui_main_window.h" e "src/editor/ui_main_window.h"

chapter 3 - "Creating Menus and Toolbars"



Use a splitter. chapter 4 - "The Central Widget"

Another way of using multiple widgets together is to use a QSplitter. The QSplitter arranges its child widgets horizontally or vertically, with splitter handles to give some sizing control to the user. Splitters can contain all kinds of widgets, including other splitters.



generate source code from form:

ex:
uic -o ui_main_window.h main_window.ui



adicionar arquivo ao projeto:

QtCreator->Help->qmake Manual

adicionar os novos arquivos ao .pro

gerar novo Makefile:

qmake -o Makefile lgmx.pro

Criar novo Dialog:

Select File/New ...; then from Files and Classes, pick Qt, and select Qt Designer Form Class from the right-hand-side panel. Choose ... then takes you to another page where you can select a Dialog.

In the 'File menu' :
New file or project
Files and classes : Qt
Qt Designer Form class

